message.content:
cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LG

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper presents an automated theorem prover for classical higher-order logic with Henkin semantics and choice. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as automated theorem proving is a subfield of AI. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the prover supports rank-1 polymorphism and natively supports almost every normal higher-order modal logic. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the prover produces verifiable proof certificates. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions the use of translations to (polymorphic) many-sorted first-order logic, which is a common technique in machine learning.
